The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Aug. 24: The 

 government today said it will not hesitate to take further 

 fiscal steps to check inflation, which has risen to 4.10 

 per cent, but said augmenting farm production is the only 

 way to check rising prices of vegetables and other food 

 articles. Finance minister P. Chidambaram said prices of 

 essential commodities had risen because of stagnant output.

 Mumbai, Aug. 24: Cipla 

 plans to spend Rs 930 crore for expansion including new 

 manufacturing units in the next two years. The company 

 also denied reports of a possible takeover by Mukesh Ambanis 

 Reliance Lifesciences.

 New Delhi, Aug. 24: A 

 group of ministers looking into the means to vacate spectrum 

 by defence forces for use in mobile services is likely to 

 meet on September 7. Prior to the meeting, telecom secretary 

 D.S. Mathur will meet his defence ministry counterpart.

 Mumbai, Aug. 24: Sebi 

 today decided to introduce a fast track mechanism for issuing 

 securities, which would allow listed companies to raise 

 funds from the markets in the least possible time.

 New Delhi, Aug. 24: Infotech 

 Enterprises plans to invest Rs 60 crore to set up a technology 

 park in Hyderabad. It is also eyeing acquisitions in the 

 US and Europe to expand its business.




